---
import SectionHeading from './SectionHeading.astro';
---

<section id="research" class="section-padding bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-900">
  <div class="container-max">
    <div class="fade-in-up">
      <SectionHeading
        title="Research"
        subtitle="Contributions to machine learning and computer vision."
      />
    </div>

    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto space-y-8">

      <!-- Research paper -->
      <div class="fade-in-up bg-white dark:bg-gray-950 rounded-2xl p-6 border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-800 hover:border-indigo-300 dark:hover:border-indigo-700 transition-all hover:shadow-md">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-start justify-between gap-3 mb-4">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
            <div class="p-2.5 rounded-xl bg-indigo-50 dark:bg-indigo-950 text-indigo-600 dark:text-indigo-400 flex-shrink-0">
              <svg class="h-5 w-5" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M9 12h6m-6 4h6m2 5H7a2 2 0 01-2-2V5a2 2 0 012-2h5.586a1 1 0 01.707.293l5.414 5.414a1 1 0 01.293.707V19a2 2 0 01-2 2z" />
              </svg>
            </div>
            <div>
              <span class="inline-block px-2.5 py-0.5 rounded-full text-xs font-semibold bg-green-100 dark:bg-green-950 text-green-700 dark:text-green-300 border border-green-200 dark:border-green-800">
                B.Tech Thesis
              </span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <a
            href="https://github.com/Najmussakib93/Attentive-Normalized-Generation-of-Images-from-Semantic-Layout-Information"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
            class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 text-xs font-semibold text-indigo-600 dark:text-indigo-400 hover:underline"
          >
            <svg class="h-4 w-4" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M12 2C6.477 2 2 6.484 2 12.017c0 4.425 2.865 8.18 6.839 9.504.5.092.682-.217.682-.483 0-.237-.008-.868-.013-1.703-2.782.605-3.369-1.343-3.369-1.343-.454-1.158-1.11-1.466-1.11-1.466-.908-.62.069-.608.069-.608 1.003.07 1.531 1.032 1.531 1.032.892 1.53 2.341 1.088 2.91.832.092-.647.35-1.088.636-1.338-2.22-.253-4.555-1.113-4.555-4.951 0-1.093.39-1.988 1.029-2.688-.103-.253-.446-1.272.098-2.65 0 0 .84-.27 2.75 1.026A9.564 9.564 0 0112 6.844c.85.004 1.705.115 2.504.337 1.909-1.296 2.747-1.027 2.747-1.027.546 1.379.202 2.398.1 2.651.64.7 1.028 1.595 1.028 2.688 0 3.848-2.339 4.695-4.566 4.943.359.309.678.92.678 1.855 0 1.338-.012 2.419-.012 2.747 0 .268.18.58.688.482A10.019 10.019 0 0022 12.017C22 6.484 17.522 2 12 2z" clip-rule="evenodd" />
            </svg>
            Paper / Code
          </a>
        </div>

        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-2">
          Attentive-Normalized Generation of Images for Semantic Layout Information
        </h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 mb-4">
          NIT Warangal — Computer Science & Engineering
        </p>

        <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 leading-relaxed mb-5">
          Designed and implemented a novel GAN architecture for layout-to-image synthesis, introducing
          <strong class="text-gray-900 dark:text-white">Attentive Normalization (AN)</strong> to improve feature attention
          and semantic consistency in generated images — addressing a key limitation of prior work
          such as Layout2Im and pix2pix.
        </p>

        <div class="space-y-2 mb-5">
          {[
            'Built a multi-stage generator (Object Composer → Encoder → convLSTM-based Object Fuser → Decoder) with dual discriminators, integrating KL-divergence, adversarial, and classification losses',
            'Trained on MS COCO (70k+ images) with GPU acceleration — achieved FID 38.02 vs. 38.14 baseline and 50.7% vs. 49.8% object classification accuracy over Layout2Im',
            'Applied the framework to class imbalance correction: generated synthetic samples for CIFAR-10, improving ResNet-110 classification across severely imbalanced classes',
            'Demonstrated broader applications: forensic scene reconstruction, rapid prototyping in design and advertising',
          ].map((point) => (
            <div class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">
              <span class="text-indigo-500 mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0">▸</span>
              {point}
            </div>
          ))}
        </div>

        <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2">
          {['Python', 'PyTorch', 'GANs', 'convLSTM', 'CNNs', 'MS COCO', 'CIFAR-10', 'Computer Vision'].map((t) => (
            <span class="px-2.5 py-0.5 rounded-md text-xs font-medium bg-indigo-50 dark:bg-indigo-950 text-indigo-700 dark:text-indigo-300 border border-indigo-100 dark:border-indigo-900">
              {t}
            </span>
          ))}
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Disaster NLP research -->
      <div class="fade-in-up bg-white dark:bg-gray-950 rounded-2xl p-6 border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-800 hover:border-indigo-300 dark:hover:border-indigo-700 transition-all hover:shadow-md">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-4">
          <div class="p-2.5 rounded-xl bg-purple-50 dark:bg-purple-950 text-purple-600 dark:text-purple-400 flex-shrink-0">
            <svg class="h-5 w-5" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M9 12h6m-6 4h6m2 5H7a2 2 0 01-2-2V5a2 2 0 012-2h5.586a1 1 0 01.707.293l5.414 5.414a1 1 0 01.293.707V19a2 2 0 01-2 2z" />
            </svg>
          </div>
          <span class="inline-block px-2.5 py-0.5 rounded-full text-xs font-semibold bg-purple-100 dark:bg-purple-950 text-purple-700 dark:text-purple-300 border border-purple-200 dark:border-purple-800">
            Research Assistantship
          </span>
        </div>

        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-2">
          NLP-Based Disaster Event Detection from Social Media
        </h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 mb-4">
          Lamar University — Mar 2024 to Oct 2024
        </p>

        <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 leading-relaxed mb-5">
          Applied machine learning and NLP to classify disaster-related tweets in near real-time,
          supporting early warning systems and community resilience.
        </p>

        <div class="space-y-2 mb-5">
          {[
            'Scraped and compiled 27,000+ disaster-related tweets across 9 major events (2011–2019) using BeautifulSoup and Python',
            'Engineered labeled datasets for supervised ML — tweet text, timestamps, relevance classification',
            'Applied Logistic Regression, SVM, and LSTM to classify disaster tweets, flagging events within an average of 4 minutes',
          ].map((point) => (
            <div class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">
              <span class="text-purple-500 mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0">▸</span>
              {point}
            </div>
          ))}
        </div>

        <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2">
          {['Python', 'NLP', 'LSTM', 'SVM', 'BeautifulSoup', 'Scikit-learn', 'Pandas'].map((t) => (
            <span class="px-2.5 py-0.5 rounded-md text-xs font-medium bg-purple-50 dark:bg-purple-950 text-purple-700 dark:text-purple-300 border border-purple-100 dark:border-purple-900">
              {t}
            </span>
          ))}
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>
  </div>
</section>
